Work that was done during visit to trap (luVisitType)

codeDefinition.definition: Start trap and begin trapping [Used when trap had not been operating, or when it is moved or reconfigured. Defines the beginning of a sampling period. Fish are never processed during this type of visit.]

Continue trapping in same position and configuration without interruption [Used when there is no break in trap operations. Defines the break between two sampling periods. Fish are usually processed during this type of visit.]

Unplanned restart of trap after malfunction (in same position and configuration) [Used when the trap had stopped operating. Defines the break between two sampling periods. Fish are usually processed during this type of visit.]
End trapping in current position or configuration [Used when trap is moved or stopped. Defines the end of a sampling period. Fish are usually processed during this type of visit.]

"Drive by" [Trap is scanned to ensure it is functioning, but fish are not processed and trap is not adjusted. Environmental measures may be taken. If a "drive by" results in fish being sampled or trap being serviced, then use an alternative code as appropriate. Does not define the beginning or end of a sampling period.]

Service / adjust / clean trap [Adjustment is made to trap during a sampling period, such as returning it to desired sampling position or removing debris. Does not define the beginning or end of a sampling period. Fish are not processed during this type of visit.]

codeDefinition.definition: No fish were caught [If no fish were caught, use this code and enter a record with n=0 for each targeted taxon.]

No catch data; fish released [No records in CatchRaw should exist.]
